premise_source_doc_sentence: Joseph Carey Merrick  (  5 August 1862 -- 11 April 1890 ; often incorrectly called John Merrick  )  was an English man with very severe deformities who was first exhibited at a freak show as the `` Elephant Man '' , and then went to live at the London Hospital after he met Frederick Treves , so becoming well known in London society .
